# .cursorignore Template

## Purpose

Exclude files from Cursor IDE's AI context. Reduces noise, improves AI response quality, and protects sensitive information from being sent to AI models.

## Official Documentation

- [Cursor Documentation](https://cursor.com/docs) - IDE documentation
- Similar to `.gitignore` syntax

## When to Use

- ✅ Teams using Cursor IDE for AI-assisted development
- ✅ Large codebases with many generated/vendored files
- ✅ Projects with sensitive data that shouldn't be in AI context
- ✅ Monorepos where AI should focus on specific areas

## When NOT to Use

- ❌ Teams not using Cursor IDE
- ❌ Small projects where full context is beneficial

## Required Marker Files

- None (optional for any Cursor user)

## Trade-offs & Alternatives

| Alternative | When to Use Instead |
|-------------|---------------------|
| Project-specific context | When you want AI to focus on certain files |
| Cursor settings | For user-level (not project-level) ignores |

