## Best Practices

### Keep AI-Relevant Files Visible
```gitignore
# DON'T ignore these (AI needs them for context):
# - Source code (src/, lib/)
# - Config files (tsconfig.json, package.json)
# - Documentation (README.md, docs/*.md) - unless very large
# - Test files (AI can help write tests)
```

### Be Careful with Wildcards
```gitignore
# Too aggressive - ignores config files
# *.json

# Better - specific ignores
package-lock.json
*.generated.json
data/*.json
```

### Project-Specific Tuning

Large monorepo? Ignore other teams' code:
```gitignore
# Focus on my team's area
packages/other-team/
apps/legacy/
```

## Common Pitfalls

❌ **Don't ignore:**
- Source code (defeats the purpose of AI assistance)
- Config files (AI needs to understand project setup)
- README.md (context for the project)
- Test files (AI can help write/fix tests)

✅ **Do ignore:**
- Dependencies (external code)
- Generated files (derived from source)
- Large data files (consume context)
- Binaries (not meaningful to AI)
- Secrets (security concern)
